cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.DS, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with image processing and computer vision, specifically saliency detection in images. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The use of dense subgraphs in the algorithm suggests that it may also fall under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the use of random walks on a Markov chain, which could place it under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of features and machine learning techniques for saliency detection suggests that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
